SELECT experiment_name, algorithm_used, accuracy FROM experimental_data JOIN machine_learning_analysis ON experimental_data.id = machine_learning_analysis.data_id WHERE machine_learning_analysis.algorithm_used LIKE 'Random Forest%' ORDER BY accuracy DESC;

SELECT experiment_name, experiment_date, algorithm_used, accuracy FROM experimental_data JOIN machine_learning_analysis ON experimental_data.id = machine_learning_analysis.data_id WHERE data_type IN ('Temperature', 'Pressure') AND accuracy > 0.8 ORDER BY accuracy DESC, experiment_date DESC;
SELECT data_type, AVG(data_value) AS avg_value, COUNT(*) AS num_experiments FROM experimental_data GROUP BY data_type HAVING COUNT(*) > 5 ORDER BY avg_value DESC;
